President Biden is set to meet with Cardinal Matteo Maria Zuppi, Archbishop of Bologna and President of the Italian Episcopal Conference, at the White House on July 18. The meeting is taking place at the request of Pope Francis, and the main topic of discussion will be the suffering caused by Russia's war in Ukraine. The United States and the Holy See have been collaborating on providing humanitarian aid to those affected by the conflict, and they will also address the repatriation of Ukrainian children who were forcibly deported by Russian officials.